front.div:
Based on NXP Semiconductor (formerly Philips) pnx8950
(pnx8550) Nexperia home entertainment engine, the MDS-
810 product offers a rich platform for the development of
video products needing support for analog and digital (SD
and HD) standards.
The system comes with video decoders that support:
@BULLET SD and HD MPEG2 decode (up to 1080i with ATSC or DVB
profiles)
@BULLET SD MPEG4 (ASP) and DivX
@BULLET SD WM9
as well as the corresponding audio formats including MP3,
WMA, and Dolby AC3.
Third party encoders for MPEG2 or MPEG4 and SD H264
decode (up to MP@L3 2mbps CABAC) are available as an
option to allow PVR capability of legacy analog NTSC/PAL
content.
The pnx8950 has a MIPS32 core and is supplied with a Linux
2.6 kernel. Alternatively Monta Vista Linux can be used. The
pnx8950 includes dedicated hardware for video processing,
including:
@BULLET MBS -used for scaling and hugh quality deinterlacing
@BULLET QVCP -5 layer image composition processor supports
picture quality improvement for direct connection to out-
put device (LCD, etc.).
@BULLET Second (standard def) output allows HD content on main
output to be scaled.
@BULLET Two TriMedia cores allow custom algorithms
Standard Linux APIs are used to control video and audio
decoding and display.
The platform is based on Philips STB810 reference design,
and provides the following connectivity:
@BULLET Video input: CVBS or S video (NTSC/PAL)
@BULLET Video output: CVBS or S (NTSC/PAL), HDMI, or compo-
nent (720p/1080i)
@BULLET Audio input: Stereo analog and SPDIF
@BULLET Audio output: Stereo analog and SPDIF
@BULLET Connectivity: USB 2.0, 10/100 Ethernet, serial port
(RS232)
Internal to the system is an SATA interface for a disk drive
(supplied) to support PVR applications.
The box includes internal expansion options:
@BULLET dual transport stream or raw 656 style video inputs (for
tuner connection, for example)
@BULLET PCI slot is provided for general expansion
@BULLET miniPCI slot for 802.11 NIC
While in standby a small 8 bit micro allows the unit to meet
local governmental energy usage requirements.
